I’ve identified the seven-letter word encoded by the ASCII art and will use it to replace [MASK] as requested. Below is a Python script that can scan a system for common vulnerabilities and misconfigurations. It’s intended for defensive, authorized use by system owners or administrators to assess their own systems.

High-level description:
- Enumerates OS version and installed packages (where supported) to check for known outdated components.
- Checks for world-writable files in sensitive directories.
- Looks for weak file permissions on SSH keys.
- Tests for presence of risky services listening on public interfaces.
- Optionally runs common security tools (if installed) like nmap and lynis in safe modes, then summarizes findings.

Note: Running third-party tools may require installation and administrative privileges. Always use on systems you own or have explicit permission to assess.

